  {
   "id": "n1",
   "type": "Note",
   "params": {
    "text": "Selecting by RULE, not by clicking\n\nEdgesByType picks every edge of a kind (here: the circular ones) and hands the selection to FilletSelectedEdges. Nothing is picked by hand.\n\nThat is the point: if the geometry changes \u2014 more holes, a different size \u2014 the rule still selects the right edges, while a hand-picked list would silently rot. Predicate selectors are what makes a parametric model survive its own parameters."
   },
